    "actor_description": "I can't settle. My thoughts keep circling the same possibilities, each one a little worse than the last. I catch myself checking the room again—hands busy, feet shifting, jaw tight—as if motion could keep the feeling from landing.",
    "description_text": "{actor} fidgets with restless energy—small movements that don't resolve into action, eyes tracking the room with a worried, distracted focus.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear uneven breathing and little sounds of restlessness—footsteps that start and stop, a quiet exhale that doesn't fully release.",
        "olfactory": "I smell a faint edge of stress-sweat, the kind that comes from holding yourself together."
    },
